    "notes": "Establishes Centers for Faith-Based and Community Initiatives within five Cabinet departments, supervised by the same-day-established White House OFBCI, to audit and remove barriers to faith-based organizations' participation in federal social-service delivery. Scores 33.33% (4/12), driven by concentrated White House coordination (Flag1), internal-only (non-public/non-Congressional) reporting (Flag2), and broad discretionary hedging (Flag4) - the founding operational order of a defining administration initiative (Flag9)."
