    "notes": "Bans project-labor-agreement requirements/prohibitions in federal and federally-funded construction contracting, reviving GHW Bush's EO12818 (this stream, Batch 8: 40.0%) and reversing Clinton's EO12836 (this stream: 16.67%). Scores 35.71% (5/14) - continues this stream's tracked PLA partisan-reversal cycle (Flag9), with a notably well-limited exemption clause (Flag11) that explicitly excludes labor-dispute-based justifications, a rare example of an exemption architecture designed with its own guardrail against a specific circumvention risk."
  },
