    "notes": "Declares a new national emergency and blocks property of persons threatening Western Balkans stabilization efforts (extremist violence undermining the Dayton Accords and UNSCR 1244 Kosovo implementation). Scores 50.0% (7/14) - the SIXTH independent confirmation of this stream's 'new blocking-order emergency' punitive template (after EO12957 Iran, EO13067 Sudan, EO13088 Kosovo, EO13129 Taliban, and EO13194 Sierra Leone diamonds, all this stream), and the first from the Bush administration. Notable for reaching the identical 50.0% score via a DIFFERENT flag composition than the original four Clinton-era instances: explicit Congressional transmittal is now present (Flag2 ABSENT, reflecting more consistent Bush-era drafting practice, also seen at EO13213 this chunk) while Flag11 shifts to PRESENT (a pointed exclusion of the humanitarian-donation exemption), exactly offsetting - a clean confirmation the template generalizes across drafting-convention changes."
